title: Noatak National Preserve: Birds
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     Nature     Animals     Birds                Birds         Arctic tern flying in Noatak National Preserve. NPS Photo  Don't forget your binoculars! Northwest Alaska is a premier place to view migratory birds. With travelers from all seven continents, this part of the world hosts nesting birds from around the world each summer. Contact the visitor center to get some more information about our bird list at (907)442-3890.
